The paper deals with approximation algorithms for the Traveling Salesman Problem (TSP) in graphs, which is a classic problem in computer science. The paper specifically focuses on the Graphic TSP problem, which involves finding the shortest Hamiltonian cycle in a graph where the edges represent distances between nodes. The paper uses techniques from graph theory and combinatorics to develop new approximation algorithms for this problem. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
